<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Twin_paradox&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<dl>
<dt>The ideal clock</dt>
</dl>
<p>The <i>ideal clock</i> is a clock whose action depends only on its instantaneous velocity, and is independent of any acceleration of the clock. <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWolfgang_Rindler2006">Wolfgang Rindler (2006). <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=0J_dwCmQThgC&amp;pg=PA43" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=0J_dwCmQThgC&amp;pg=PA43" rel="nofollow">"Time dilation"</a>. <i>Relativity: Special, General, and Cosmological</i>. Oxford University Press. p.&#160;43. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0198567316" class="internal">ISBN 0198567316</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=0J_dwCmQThgC&amp;pg=PA43" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=0J_dwCmQThgC&amp;pg=PA43" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=0J_dwCmQThgC&amp;pg=PA43</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Time+dilation&amp;rft.atitle=Relativity%3A+Special%2C+General%2C+and+Cosmological&amp;rft.aulast=Wolfgang+Rindler&amp;rft.au=Wolfgang+Rindler&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B43&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0198567316&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D0J_dwCmQThgC%26pg%3DPA43&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Twin_paradox"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></p>
<dl>
<dt>Gravitational time dilation; time dilation in circular motion</dt>
</dl>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFJohn_A_Peacock2001">John A Peacock (2001). <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=t8O-yylU0j0C&amp;pg=PA7" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=t8O-yylU0j0C&amp;pg=PA7" rel="nofollow">Cosmological Physics</a></i>. Cambridge University Press. p.&#160;8. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521422701" class="internal">ISBN 0521422701</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=t8O-yylU0j0C&amp;pg=PA7" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=t8O-yylU0j0C&amp;pg=PA7" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=t8O-yylU0j0C&amp;pg=PA7</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Cosmological+Physics&amp;rft.aulast=John+A+Peacock&amp;rft.au=John+A+Peacock&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B8&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0521422701&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dt8O-yylU0j0C%26pg%3DPA7&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Twin_paradox"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
